        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(apple): localize native app surfaces",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nThe Apple apps had only partial English/Russian/Hindi catalog coverage, while the Share Extension, Activity Widget, and Watch app were not wired to the catalog.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nExpand the iOS and macOS String Catalogs to English plus the complete 20-locale native matrix, wire the shared iOS catalog into the main app, Share Extension, Activity Widget, and Watch app, and route Share Extension actions/status/errors through `NSLocalizedString`.\n\n## User Impact\n\nGateway setup/navigation/chat/settings strings, native watch chat/approval labels, activity status text, share actions, and macOS controls can render in every supported native locale. Catalog checks fail if any locale/key is missing.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- `node --import tsx scripts/apple-app-i18n.ts check` (`44` catalog keys)\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs test/scripts/apple-app-i18n.test.ts`\n- `swiftformat --lint --config config/swiftformat apps/ios/ShareExtension/ShareViewController.swift`\n- `git diff --check`\n\nXcodeGen and full Apple builds remain host-dependent. This PR is stacked on #97110.",
